{\pard\sl-41\slmult0\par

{\pard\plain \li5280\sl233\slmult1 \ri0\nooverflow\qj{\f11\fs20 be described by low level descriptors that aim to mimic semantic content of the image and make it understandable for computers.}\par}
}
{\pard\sl-342\slmult0\par

{\pard\plain \li5280\sl-233\slmult0 \ri0\nooverflow\qj\fi199 {\f11\fs20 In the study presented in this paper, each feature is investigated independently before being combined with other features. Features are evaluated using statistical methods as well as individual classi cation results. Sta-tistical evidence is gathered primarily from the training set as inclusive or exclusive validation runs. This further provides insight into how representative is the feature for images of the same category. Classi cation results are generated from an exclusive subset of the training set as well as the test set.}\par}
}
{\pard\sl-343\slmult0\par

{\pard\plain \li5280\sl-231\slmult0 \ri0\nooverflow\qj\fi199 {\f11\fs19 The following of the paper is organized as follows. In sec-tion II, our global approach chosen to solve scene recogni-tion problem is explained. Sections III, IV and V respec-tively detail how Gabor, {Centrist} and color histogram feature descriptors are de ned and used to describe the im-age. Obtained feature vectors are combined in section VI and their performance is evaluated. Section VII concludes this paper and summarizes the best results obtained.}\par}
}\sect\sbkpage\sectd\pard\plain
