\pard\sl-386\slmult0\par

{\pard\plain \li0\sl-228\slmult0 \ri0\nooverflow\qj{\f11\fs20 image blocks (for this project, xed 4x4 grid of sub-regions over the map was considered) [5]. Thus, the size of feature vector is 1x576: 4x4 grid (16 windows where average values is computed) x 12 ( lters in the Gabor bank) x 3 (number of color planes for RGB image).}\par}
}
{\pard\sl-213\slmult0\par

{\pard\plain \li0\sl-229\slmult0 \ql{\f11\fs20 4.3 Classi cation Results}\par}
}
{\pard\sl-145\slmult0\par

{\pard\plain \li0\sl-233\slmult0 \ri0\nooverflow\qj\fi199 {\f11\fs19 Similarly to previous approaches, MLP neural network with single hidden layer was considered as a classi er. All images form the training set were converted into 1x576x69 feature matrixes for each category (1x576 feature vector, 69 images in each category in the training set). Then train-ing matrices were converted into input matrix 576x345. The corresponding target matrix has 5x345 for the train-ing set and 5x150 for the testing set. Testing matrix size is 576x150 (testing set contains 150 images). Training set was divided into three categories: training (70% of train-ing images), validation (15%) and testing (15%).}\par}
}
{\pard\sl-45\slmult0\par

{\pard\plain \li0\ri0\nooverflow\qj{\f11\fs20 The number of input neurons is equal to the number of features in the feature vector: 576. The number of hidden nodes was found experimentally and the value of 300 was the optimal number of hidden nodes. The number of out-puts is the number of categories: 5 classes of scenes in the dataset.}\par}
}
{\pard\sl-52\slmult0\par

{\pard\plain \li0\sl-227\slmult0 \ri0\nooverflow\qj\fi199 {\f11\fs18 Overall classi cation accuracy with Gabor-{Gist} features on 150 training set reached 86%. Error rate di ers from category to category, for example Forest images were classi-ed correctly in 100% of cases, when Highway had the low-}\par}
}\sect\sbkpage\sectd\pard\plain
