{\pard\plain \li0\sl-229\slmult0 \ri0\nooverflow\qj{\f11\fs19 est accuracy - only 70% of correctly classi ed images. See confusion matrix in gure 5 for more details. Comparably to Gabor histogram approaches, Gabor-{Gist} over color image performed signi cantly better. Hence, Gabor-{Gist} features will be used for the hybrid feature vector creation.}\par}
}
{\pard\sl-204\slmult0\par

{\pard\plain \li1260\sl239\slmult1 \ql{\f9\fs20 IV. Centrist Descriptor}\par}
}
{\pard\sl-107\slmult0\par

{\pard\plain \li0\sl239\slmult1 \ql{\f17\fs20 IV.1. Computation of CT Value}\par}
}
{\pard\sl-141\slmult0\par

{\pard\plain \li0\sl-229\slmult0 \ri0\nooverflow\qj\fi199 {\f11\fs19 CENsus TRansform hISTogram ({Centrist}), is a visual descriptor used to identify scene categories [6]. The {Cen-}trist {feature vector is perfectly suitable for scene classi -} cation because this descriptor encodes the structural prop-erties of a given image without keeping the detailed textu-ral information that would not be helpful for this problem.}\par}
}
{\pard\sl-46\slmult0\par

{\pard\plain \li0\sl226\slmult1 \ri0\nooverflow\qj\fi118 {\f11\fs20 The {Centrist} feature vector of a given image is calcu-lated in 2 distinct steps:}\par}
}
{\pard\sl-55\slmult0\par

{\pard\plain \li400\sl226\slmult1 \ri0\nooverflow\ql\fi-199 {\f11\fs20 1. First, the CT value for each pixel is computed. This is performed by a call to {Matlab} function {compare.m}}\par}
}
