{\pard\plain \li0\sl221\slmult1 \ri0\nooverflow\qj{\f8\fs16 Fig. 13. Confusion matrix for Gabor + CENTRIST hybrid features. 1-Coast; 2-Forest; 3-Highway; 4-Mountain; 5-Tall Building}\par}
}
{\pard\sl-200\slmult0\par
\pard\sl-250\slmult0\par

{\pard\plain \li0\sl-231\slmult0 \ri0\nooverflow\qj{\f11\fs20 in gure 13. It indicates potential improvement from com-bining the features together (if mutual classi cation com-pensation occurs). On practice, signi cant classi cation error disease occurred, and overall accuracy raised from 86% ( gure 5) to 93.3%( gure 13). Features compensated each other de ciencies and didn't create any noticeable confusion.}\par}
}
{\pard\sl-191\slmult0\par

{\pard\plain \li0\sl239\slmult1 \ql{\f11\fs20 2.2 Gabor + Color Histogram Hybrid Results}\par}
}
{\pard\sl-134\slmult0\par

{\pard\plain \li0\sl256\slmult1 \ri0\nooverflow\qj\fi199 {\f11\fs19 Our team was pretty sceptical about combining color histograms with features extracted with other methods, as color histograms performed poorly. The guess was that color histogram features would add more confusion than do any good. However, experiments demonstrated slight per-formance improvement from 86% accuracy (Gabor-{Gist} only) to 89.3% (Gabor-{Gist} and color histogram). Gabor-Gist {and color histogram hybrid improved the correct}}\par}
}\sect\sbkpage\sectd\pard\plain
