\pard\sl-238\slmult0\par

{\pard\plain \li0\sl227\slmult1 \ri0\nooverflow\qj{\f8\fs16 Fig. 14. Confusion Matrix for Gabor-{Gist} + {Centrist} + Color his-togram hybrid features. 1-Coast; 2-Forest; 3-Highway; 4-Mountain; 5-Tall Building}\par}
}
{\pard\sl-200\slmult0\par
\pard\sl-254\slmult0\par

{\pard\plain \li0\sl-223\slmult0 \ri0\nooverflow\qj{\f11\fs20 classi cation rate for Coast, Highway and Mountain cat-egories. However, performance decreased for Forest and Tall Building scene classes.}\par}
}
{\pard\sl-196\slmult0\par

{\pard\plain \li0\sl239\slmult1 \ql{\f11\fs20 2.3 {Centrist} + Color Histogram Hybrid Results}\par}
}
{\pard\sl-137\slmult0\par

{\pard\plain \li0\sl-232\slmult0 \ri0\nooverflow\qj\fi199 {\f11\fs20 Adding the color histogram descriptor to {Centrist} also improved the classi cation accuracy. Improvement oc-curred for Coast, Forest and Mountain categories but a performance decrease was observed for Highway and Tall Building scene classes. Not that for both Gabor-{Gist} and Centrist{, adding color histogram feature vector improves} Coast and Mountain correct classi cation and reduces Tall building classi cation. However, the behaviour di ers for Highway and Forest images.}\par}
}
{\pard\sl-235\slmult0\par
{{\listtext{\pard\plain {\f11\fs20 2.4 }\tab}}\pard\plain 
\f11\fs20 \qj\fi-359\nowidctlpar\jclisttab\tx360\faauto\ls3\ilvl0\rin0\nooverflow\lin360\itap0 {\plain\f11\fs20 Gabor + {Centrist} + Color Histogram Hybrid Re-sults }\par}
}
{\pard\sl-340\slmult0\par

{\pard\plain \li0\sl-233\slmult0 \ri0\nooverflow\qj\fi199 {\f11\fs20 Finally, all the features extracted with the three meth-ods studied in this work (Gabor-{Gist}, {Centrist} and color histogram) were combined. As expected, this is the combi-nation that performed the best. Compared to Gabor-{Gist} + {Centrist} hybrid, the classi cation accuracy increased from 93.3% ( gure 13) to 95.3% ( gure 14). Signi cant improvement occurred for Highway category (83.3% cate-gory accuracy to 96.6%), and slight accuracy decrease was demonstrated in Coast category (93.3% to 90% class accu-racy).}\par}
}
{\pard\sl-197\slmult0\par

{\pard\plain \li1700\sl239\slmult1 \ql{\f9\fs20 VII. Conclusion}\par}
}
{\pard\sl-137\slmult0\par

{\pard\plain \li0\sl-229\slmult0 \ri0\nooverflow\qj\fi199 {\f11\fs19 This paper shows that combining Gabor-{Gist} descrip-tor with {Centrist} and color histogram feature vectors is particularly e cient for scene classi cation. Indeed, the accuracy obtained using a Neural Network as a classi er is above 95% for the provided dataset of images. This very high rate of correctly classi ed images is made possible by}\par}
}\column

{\pard\sl-200\slmult0\par
\pard\sl-210\slmult0\par

{\pard\plain \li7\sl-226\slmult0 \ri0\nooverflow\qj{\f11\fs20 the complementarity of the methods used: because Gabor-Gist{,} Centrist {and color histogram have their maximum} e ciency for di erent categories, the overall accuracy is in-creased when they are combined.}\par}
}
{\pard\sl-44\slmult0\par

{\pard\plain \li7\sl-226\slmult0 \ri0\nooverflow\qj{\f11\fs20 Finally, we can say that this combination of three descrip-tors is very interesting and competitive when compared to other existing methods that can be found in scene classi - cation papers.}\par}
}
{\pard\sl-182\slmult0\par

{\pard\plain \li1947\sl239\slmult1 \ql{\f9\fs20 References}\par}
}
